    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-02-20T19:04:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-02-20T19:04:00-05:00" n="200"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d200">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">315/2–2053: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The United States Representative at the United Nations</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="#p_LODGEHCJ1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lodge</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-02-20T19:04:00-05:00"
                            >February 20, 1953—7:04 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>541. For <persName corresp="#p_HICKERSONJD1">Hickerson</persName>, <gloss
                        target="#t_UNA1">UNA</gloss>. Please find out whether
                        <persName>Boheman</persName> (Sweden) would be available for position of
                    United Nations Secretary General.<note n="1" xml:id="d200fn1">
                        <p>In telegram 940, Feb. 21, 1953, 1:52 p.m., to Stockholm, the Department
                            cabled, <persName corresp="#p_HICKERSONJD1">Hickerson</persName> to
                            Ambassador <persName>Butterworth</persName>: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“Please ascertain discreetly from <gloss target="#t_FonOff1"
                                        >FonOff</gloss>, and of course without commitment on our
                                    part, whether <persName>Boheman</persName> would be available
                                    for post <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> Secretary General.”
                                    (315/2–2053)</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                    </note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LODGEHCJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lodge</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
